course_metadata.title: Green house by using IoT and cloud computing

content_chunks.content: The course provides introduction to green aspect, as well as to greenhouse technology. The benefits and problems of green buildings are analysed. Green Buildings examples in Lithuania and other countries are provided for better understanding of greenhouse technology and its implementation. Other topics are analysed in the course: Green house by using IoT and cloud computing; green building certification (BREEM, LEAD and etc.); Smart systems application in green buildings (home automation system; health monitoring system; weather reporting system and etc.).

Green building technology for sustainable and environmentally conscious construction - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in implementing IoT-enabled smart systems and cloud computing solutions for energy-efficient building management. Students master green building certification processes (BREEAM, LEED), building automation systems, and smart sensor networks that optimize resource consumption and enhance occupant comfort. The curriculum covers IoT-based health monitoring, weather reporting systems, smart anti-theft technologies, and intelligent waste management solutions for sustainable buildings. Graduates emerge skilled in developing connected healthcare systems, smart cradle technologies, and streetlight monitoring solutions that contribute to environmentally responsible architecture while improving building performance and user experience through advanced digital integration.
